-- RadioShack shareholder says in talks to improve liquidity
-- By Ramkumar Iyer in Bangalore
-- Fri Sep 26, 2014 10:59AM EDT
-- None



Sept 26 (Reuters) - Hedge fund Standard General LP said it was in talks with RadiShack Corp <RSH.N> to improve the troubled electronics retailer's liquidity ahead of the holiday season.

RadioShack's shares were up 21 percent at 96 cents in morning trading on the New York Stock Exchange. Standard General, which raised its stake in RadioShack to 9.8 percent from 7.08 percent to become the largest shareholder, said its proposals include purchasing the company's loans and other commitments under its credit facility. [ID:nEOL3wnLnC]